content:
The code chunk demonstrates how to replace a texture across a model in Panda3D 1.10.4 using the `replace_texture` method, providing an efficient alternative to manually setting textures on individual parts of a C++ car model.

cpp

NodePath car = window->load_model(window->get_render(), "bvw-f2004--carnsx/carnsx.egg");
PT(Texture) red = TexturePool::load_texture("bvw-f2004--carnsx/carnsx.png");
PT(Texture) blue = TexturePool::load_texture("bvw-f2004--carnsx/carnsx-blue.png");
car.replace_texture(red, blue);

If you are interested in changing the image of a texture during program execution, say to adjust some of its pixels, see creating-new-textures-from-scratch.
